I"F<ol>
  <li>
    <p>In another context Tarrou notes that, on coming home in the evenings, he invariably saw the night watchman pacing the hall, like a sentry <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="on his beat - (beat - 巡逻区域)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(在他的巡逻区域)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>He often asked Tarrou to say how long he thought the epidemic would last. “They say,” Tarrou informed him, “that cold weather <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="stamps out"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(根除或破坏)</code></b> diseases of this type.” The manager looked aghast.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Moreover, he was sure that for a long while to come travelers would give the town a wide berth. This epidemic <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="spelt"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(意味着/招致)</code></b> the ruin of the tourist trade, in fact.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>In the early days, travellers, unable to leave the town, had <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="kept on"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(继续租用房子[套房]等)</code></b> their rooms.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>On inquiry it <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="came out"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(被人所知/泄露)</code></b> that Mme. Othon was in quarantine; she had been nursing her mother, who had <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="succumbed to"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(死于)</code></b> plague.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>One morning there had been gunshots in the street and, as Tarrou put it, “some <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="gobs of lead - (gobs of - a lot of)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(几颗子弹)</code></b>” had <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="killed off"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(大量杀死/大量消灭[动植物])</code></b> most of the cats and scared away the others; anyhow they were no longer about.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>A <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="good"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(好的/高品质的/高水准的)</code></b> bad shock, and <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="there you are"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(这下对了/这下好了)</code></b>! you count the dead and living, and that’s an end of it.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Tarrou pointed out that, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="if it came to that - (came to - 达到某一点或状态)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(这样的话)</code></b>, everyone was “under suspicion.” But the manager had his own ideas and was not to be <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="shaken out of - (shake someone out of - 使摒弃/使改变态度/信念)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________([对某种信念/想法]动摇)</code></b> them.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“That fine gentleman will pass out with his clothes on. All dressed up and ready to go. So <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="he won’t need no laying-out - (双重否定句-动词位于两个否定词之间，那么第二个否定词表示加强或强调否定的意思)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(他不需要换寿衣了)</code></b>.”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>In the first case, habits have not yet been lost; in the second, they’re returning. It is <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="in the thick of"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(在最活跃或最激烈的部分)</code></b> a calamity that one <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="gets hardened to the truth - (hardened - 麻木不仁)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(对现实习以为常)</code></b>—in other words, to silence. So let’s wait.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
